==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sycee
<hw>Sy*cee"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Said to be from a
Chinese word, <ets>se-tze</ets> or <ets>se-sze</ets>, meaning, fine
silk, and to be so called because if pure it may be drawn out into fine
threads.]</ety> <def>Silver, pounded into ingots of the shape of a shoe,
and used as currency. The most common weight is about one pound
troy.</def> <mark>[China]</mark> <rj><au>McElrath.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sychnocarpous</ent>⟦br⟧
